WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.370 --> 00:00:05.173
Here, I was asked if I need
a special introduction, but

00:00:05.173 --> 00:00:07.356
I don't think it's necessary.

00:00:07.356 --> 00:00:13.033
I am Friar Ivan, the parish priest
of this basilica, this church, this

00:00:13.033 --> 00:00:19.583
parish, and also of the parish of Saint
Maximilian Kolbe in Bijenik, which is an

00:00:19.583 --> 00:00:24.823
extension of the parish of Saint Anthony
towards Šestine, towards the foothills.

00:00:24.823 --> 00:00:30.500
And today I will try to reflect
and speak with you about Saint

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:33.120
Anthony and the Word of God.

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:38.898
Here, this is the final topic in the
lecture series about the life of Saint

00:00:38.898 --> 00:00:43.906
Anthony, about the charisma of Saint
Anthony, and the works of Saint Anthony

00:00:43.906 --> 00:00:46.602
that you have listened to so far.

00:00:46.602 --> 00:00:51.610
First, you talked about the call of
Saint Anthony, then about the humility

00:00:51.610 --> 00:00:56.232
of Saint Anthony, about the miracles
of Saint Anthony, and about Saint

00:00:56.232 --> 00:01:00.085
Anthony and the sacraments, which
Professor Karlić covered last Thursday.

00:01:00.865 --> 00:01:08.287
What is perhaps important to say is that
no saint, nor any cycle of catechesis,

00:01:08.287 --> 00:01:12.246
can be fully covered in any given time.

00:01:12.246 --> 00:01:16.700
Above all, Saint Anthony speaks
through his closeness, his

00:01:16.700 --> 00:01:19.174
presence, and his actions today.

00:01:19.174 --> 00:01:26.597
We have made an effort and will
continue to do so, and we want to

00:01:26.597 --> 00:01:32.535
go through some segments of his
charisma, his life, his actions, his

00:01:32.535 --> 00:01:35.505
sermons, and his writings with you.

00:01:36.775 --> 00:01:43.485
At least some segments should
help us today in how we will live.

00:01:43.485 --> 00:01:50.196
In the sermons of Saint Anthony,
he says this: "Sing to the Lord

00:01:50.196 --> 00:01:53.293
a new song," says Psalm 95.

00:01:53.293 --> 00:01:57.939
That song is the knowledge
of the Holy Scriptures.

00:01:57.939 --> 00:02:05.166
All worldly knowledge aimed at profit
is an old song, the song of Babylon.

00:02:05.166 --> 00:02:11.361
Only theology is the new song, which
sweetly resonates in God's ears

00:02:11.361 --> 00:02:14.975
and only it can renew the soul.

00:02:15.815 --> 00:02:24.657
When we talk about Saint Anthony or
other saints, for example, when we say

00:02:24.657 --> 00:02:31.604
Saint Maximilian Kolbe, you've probably
heard of him, or Blessed Miroslav

00:02:31.604 --> 00:02:39.815
Bulešić or Blessed Alojzije Stepinac, we
say that they were saints and martyrs.

00:02:43.285 --> 00:02:51.150
You might have dozed off a bit, so wake
up because this isn't a one-man show.

00:02:51.150 --> 00:02:52.625
So, get involved.

00:02:52.625 --> 00:02:57.049
Saints and martyrs, when we
have an additional description

00:02:57.049 --> 00:03:03.440
of a saint, it ties to the most
important aspect of their life.

00:03:03.440 --> 00:03:09.831
So, he was a saint, okay, that means
he lived morally, lived virtuously.

00:03:09.831 --> 00:03:16.713
He wasn't sinless, that should be
clear to you, no one needs to explain

00:03:16.713 --> 00:03:23.104
that to you, that being a saint is
not synonymous with being sinless.

00:03:23.104 --> 00:03:29.003
It means that the mentioned person,
whether a male or female saint,

00:03:29.003 --> 00:03:33.920
knew how to fight their weaknesses
well, persistently and strongly.

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:39.559
A martyr, whether male or female,
means that they gave their blood,

00:03:39.559 --> 00:03:42.592
their life, for their faith in Christ.

00:03:42.592 --> 00:03:47.791
That they were killed because of
it, that they were tortured and

00:03:47.791 --> 00:03:51.691
killed because they were Catholic,
because they were Christian.

00:03:51.691 --> 00:03:57.324
Now, Saint Anthony was not a martyr,
although he greatly desired to be

00:03:57.324 --> 00:04:02.956
one, and in the first catechesis
you heard about the life of Saint

00:04:02.956 --> 00:04:04.690
Anthony, this was mentioned.

00:04:05.295 --> 00:04:09.175
That Saint Anthony left the
Augustinian order to join our

00:04:09.175 --> 00:04:11.503
Franciscan order to become a martyr.

00:04:11.503 --> 00:04:15.772
Because the bodies of the first
Franciscan martyrs, who were tortured

00:04:15.772 --> 00:04:21.205
for their faith in Christ in Morocco,
were brought to the shores of Portugal.

00:04:21.205 --> 00:04:26.250
And Saint Anthony sees this and
says, I don't want to live like

00:04:26.250 --> 00:04:32.071
this or that, no, I want to go on
missions, I want to proclaim Christ

00:04:32.071 --> 00:04:38.280
with my life, I want to lay down my
life for Christ, to shed my blood.

00:04:38.280 --> 00:04:39.467
But guess what?

00:04:39.467 --> 00:04:43.426
Saint Anthony was never particularly
a fervent missionary, nor was

00:04:43.426 --> 00:04:48.572
he ever sent on missions, and
even less so was he a martyr.

00:04:48.572 --> 00:04:54.113
When we talk about Saint Anthony on
that plaque, when you're in a church,

00:04:54.113 --> 00:04:59.259
you should learn to read and observe
the things in that church, because

00:04:59.259 --> 00:05:01.635
they are not there without reason.

00:05:01.675 --> 00:05:07.625
On that plaque over there, when you
exit the Basilica on the right side or

00:05:07.625 --> 00:05:13.971
enter on the left side, it says that the
plaque was erected on January 16, 1946.

00:05:13.971 --> 00:05:15.161
What happened then?

00:05:15.161 --> 00:05:19.921
You don't need to remember that; it's
not necessary for your salvation.

00:05:19.921 --> 00:05:25.078
But you should know that Saint
Anthony is a Doctor of the Church.

00:05:25.078 --> 00:05:30.631
So, just as Stepinac is a saint
and martyr, and Kolbe is a saint

00:05:30.631 --> 00:05:35.391
and martyr, Saint Anthony is a
saint and Doctor of the Church.

00:05:35.391 --> 00:05:36.185
This means...

00:05:36.705 --> 00:05:40.838
That his way of speaking, his way of
interpreting the Holy Scriptures—not

00:05:40.838 --> 00:05:44.282
the content, the content of the
interpretation doesn't change, but

00:05:44.282 --> 00:05:49.105
the way of interpreting, the approach
to the Word of God, the approach to

00:05:49.105 --> 00:05:52.549
preaching, the approach to theological
work—because Saint Anthony was a

00:05:52.549 --> 00:05:56.682
university professor at one of the first
universities and the first university

00:05:56.682 --> 00:06:01.505
in the world and in Europe, which is
the University of Bologna and Padua.

00:06:01.505 --> 00:06:07.358
Saint Anthony was a university professor,
and that means he brought something

00:06:07.358 --> 00:06:10.772
entirely new with his life and approach.

00:06:10.772 --> 00:06:16.138
Something entirely new, and thanks
to his way of preaching, thinking,

00:06:16.138 --> 00:06:21.992
and the way he conveyed it to
others, many souls were converted.

00:06:21.992 --> 00:06:28.333
That's why he is referred to
as a Doctor of the Church or

00:06:28.333 --> 00:06:31.260
also known as a Gospel Teacher.

00:06:31.735 --> 00:06:38.116
This quote about the new and the
old, "Sing to the Lord a new song,"

00:06:38.116 --> 00:06:44.073
refers to the old song that builds
on some old knowledge, that is, the

00:06:44.073 --> 00:06:48.753
worldly knowledge we all acquire in
various ways through our primary,

00:06:48.753 --> 00:06:50.455
secondary, and university education.

00:06:50.455 --> 00:06:55.135
This knowledge is important, it
is valuable, but of course, it

00:06:55.135 --> 00:06:59.815
is not enough to fully understand
all the reality around us.

00:07:00.565 --> 00:07:04.619
And that's why Saint Anthony
speaks about theology here.

00:07:04.619 --> 00:07:10.927
Of course, those of us who are ordained
as priests and other believers, laypeople,

00:07:10.927 --> 00:07:17.685
who wanted to learn more about their
faith or get closer to God, we completed

00:07:17.685 --> 00:07:23.541
an integrated university study, you
know how it goes, a theology study at

00:07:23.541 --> 00:07:26.245
the University of Zagreb or elsewhere.

00:07:27.570 --> 00:07:30.923
But Saint Anthony speaks
about that theology.

00:07:30.923 --> 00:07:31.881
Theos logos.

00:07:31.881 --> 00:07:36.192
These are the two components
of the word theology.

00:07:36.192 --> 00:07:39.067
Theology is any discourse about God.

00:07:39.067 --> 00:07:40.983
Any discourse about God.

00:07:40.983 --> 00:07:46.252
We have systematic theology, we
have the catechism which states and

00:07:46.252 --> 00:07:49.606
says this is how you should believe.

00:07:49.606 --> 00:07:52.001
And that is the law.

00:07:52.001 --> 00:07:52.959
No wavering.

00:07:52.959 --> 00:07:57.749
The fact that you don't understand
something from the catechism,

00:07:57.749 --> 00:08:00.145
that's not the catechism's problem.

00:08:00.145 --> 00:08:01.366
That's your problem.

00:08:01.366 --> 00:08:05.437
That's your problem because you
approach it too shallowly, without

00:08:05.437 --> 00:08:10.729
detail, expecting to just skim
the cream off the top and be done.

00:08:10.729 --> 00:08:12.765
It doesn't work that way.

00:08:12.765 --> 00:08:18.872
The truth doesn't need to conform to
you; you need to conform to the truth.

00:08:18.872 --> 00:08:24.164
And what Fr. Stjepan talked about today
regarding the Holy Spirit, open the

00:08:24.164 --> 00:08:29.864
nozzles, open the valves, so that the
Holy Spirit, who wants to give equally

00:08:29.864 --> 00:08:37.192
to everyone, to us who are here, can stir
up in you what has become sour, what has

00:08:37.192 --> 00:08:39.635
become stagnant, what has fallen asleep.

00:08:39.775 --> 00:08:45.620
And so when you're having coffee, at
weddings, wherever you go and however

00:08:45.620 --> 00:08:52.365
you spend your time, and you say,
you know, I was really bored at some

00:08:52.365 --> 00:08:58.210
spiritual retreat or I really enjoyed
the spiritual retreat or I felt great

00:08:58.210 --> 00:09:05.405
during adoration or God really spoke to me
through the song Timo Azaštito and so on.

00:09:05.405 --> 00:09:10.665
So, this is a talk about God,
a bit of theology, and that's

00:09:10.665 --> 00:09:12.688
what Saint Anthony speaks about.

00:09:12.688 --> 00:09:18.353
I have the impression that we have
a lot to say about everything, but

00:09:18.353 --> 00:09:20.781
sometimes the least about our faith.

00:09:20.781 --> 00:09:25.637
Therefore, I would like to
remind you of an event in Rimini.

00:09:25.637 --> 00:09:31.302
Rimini is a city on the Italian Adriatic
coast, which isn't really great for

00:09:31.302 --> 00:09:33.729
swimming if you've ever been there.

00:09:33.729 --> 00:09:38.181
I wouldn't recommend it much;
you might end up in trouble.

00:09:38.181 --> 00:09:42.632
Unless you've found some hidden
gem, in which case, let me

00:09:42.632 --> 00:09:45.060
know where one can swim there.

00:09:46.460 --> 00:09:47.794
It's about large cliffs.

00:09:47.794 --> 00:09:52.130
So, there are cliffs and then
you have a chasm below of, I

00:09:52.130 --> 00:09:54.131
don't know, 40-50 meters or more.

00:09:54.131 --> 00:09:55.799
Why is this event important?

00:09:55.799 --> 00:09:59.802
Because at the time when Saint
Anthony was in Rimini, he was

00:09:59.802 --> 00:10:01.136
already a famous preacher.

00:10:01.136 --> 00:10:03.471
Famous means people had heard about him.

00:10:03.471 --> 00:10:07.473
So, everyone had already heard about
him and everyone was inviting him

00:10:07.473 --> 00:10:09.475
to come and preach, proclaim, etc.

00:10:09.815 --> 00:10:16.125
And he comes to Rimini, gathers the people
there in the square or in the basilica,

00:10:16.125 --> 00:10:21.647
in the cathedral, etc. He preaches, but
they all collectively sit on their ears.

00:10:21.647 --> 00:10:24.014
And no one wants to listen.

00:10:24.014 --> 00:10:26.380
And then he loses his temper.

00:10:26.380 --> 00:10:31.508
Saints often lost their temper, if you
read the biographies of saints carefully,

00:10:31.508 --> 00:10:37.030
which I advise you to do, they often lost
their nerves, were very temperamental.

00:10:37.870 --> 00:10:42.310
The least likely to become saints
are those with slimy personalities.

00:10:42.310 --> 00:10:43.118
Remember that.

00:10:43.118 --> 00:10:47.559
Those who are more likely to
become saints are the ones

00:10:47.559 --> 00:10:49.981
who are godly, who are devout.

00:10:49.981 --> 00:10:56.441
Those who are neither here nor there, even
God doesn't know what to do with them.

00:10:56.441 --> 00:11:02.900
You let them live like that fat cat
that's 20 years old, you don't put it

00:11:02.900 --> 00:11:09.360
to sleep, you let it live, you feed it,
it drags itself around the house, wiping

00:11:09.360 --> 00:11:12.590
the dust with its belly on the floor.

00:11:12.590 --> 00:11:17.031
And Saint Anthony goes to the
shore and shouts towards the

00:11:17.031 --> 00:11:19.050
sea, preaching, and what happens?

00:11:19.050 --> 00:11:23.319
Somewhere in the distance,
fish began to gather.

00:11:23.319 --> 00:11:26.522
Fish that have three brain cells.

00:11:26.522 --> 00:11:33.460
Three brain cells, maybe I said
too much, rose above the sea to

00:11:33.460 --> 00:11:37.196
hear what Saint Anthony had to say.

00:11:37.196 --> 00:11:38.264
People, no.

00:11:38.264 --> 00:11:42.534
This is not the only case in history.

00:11:42.534 --> 00:11:49.472
We have several instances in history where
saints who were intimately connected with

00:11:49.472 --> 00:11:57.478
God, to whom nature spoke, who in their
lives returned to that old peace that

00:11:57.478 --> 00:12:01.214
existed between man and all of creation.

00:12:01.214 --> 00:12:06.017
Saint Anthony preaching to the fish,
Saint Francis befriending the wolf

00:12:06.017 --> 00:12:11.256
and resolving the situation in Gubbio
so that the foolish wolf doesn't

00:12:11.256 --> 00:12:16.932
devour the poor sheep, and in return,
the villagers will feed the wolf.

00:12:16.932 --> 00:12:20.425
That was diplomacy,
not what we hear today.

00:12:20.425 --> 00:12:21.734
That was diplomacy.

00:12:21.734 --> 00:12:27.847
So, why then, when we see a fresco
of Saint Anthony, when we see

00:12:27.847 --> 00:12:32.649
depictions of Saint Anthony in various
places, Saint Anthony is always

00:12:32.649 --> 00:12:35.269
depicted, most often in three ways.

00:12:35.269 --> 00:12:40.944
The first and most obvious is
with the child Jesus in his arms.

00:12:41.844 --> 00:12:44.760
So, with the child Jesus in his arms.

00:12:44.760 --> 00:12:46.583
The second is the lily.

00:12:46.583 --> 00:12:51.685
On that blessed coat of arms you see
throughout the basilica, I think you

00:12:51.685 --> 00:12:57.152
really have to be blind not to have
noticed that coat of arms, it says

00:12:57.152 --> 00:13:01.161
"florete quasi lilium" underneath,
which means "bloom like the lily." So,

00:13:01.161 --> 00:13:06.628
the lily is a symbol, that's why it's
the motto of the Basilica because the

00:13:06.628 --> 00:13:09.180
lily is a symbol of Saint Anthony.

00:13:09.870 --> 00:13:14.149
And the third, I wouldn't say the
most important, maybe the most

00:13:14.149 --> 00:13:18.072
important is the baby Jesus, is
the Holy Scripture, the Bible.

00:13:18.072 --> 00:13:24.134
Saint Anthony holds the Bible in his hand,
but he doesn't hold it like we do when

00:13:24.134 --> 00:13:26.631
the priest comes to bless the family.

00:13:26.631 --> 00:13:32.693
The hair I have left falls out when I
enter a family's blessing and see a Bible

00:13:32.693 --> 00:13:37.330
that evidently no one has ever opened
because it's still wrapped in cellophane.

00:13:38.210 --> 00:13:43.781
And related to that, they say, look
how beautiful and new our Bible is.

00:13:43.781 --> 00:13:46.169
I say, I see it's unopened.

00:13:46.169 --> 00:13:50.547
And then they realize that...
An untouched Bible is not a

00:13:50.547 --> 00:13:52.934
source of pride but a shame.

00:13:52.934 --> 00:13:59.700
If your Bible isn't worn out, if there are
no marks from yellowed fingers on it, if

00:13:59.700 --> 00:14:05.670
you've never underlined anything in your
Bible, you don't know what to do with it.

00:14:07.150 --> 00:14:11.306
It's understandable that sometimes we
don't know what to do with the Bible

00:14:11.306 --> 00:14:16.102
because we often make the big mistake of
starting to read it from the beginning.

00:14:16.102 --> 00:14:18.979
The Bible should not be
read from the beginning.

00:14:18.979 --> 00:14:22.496
You should start reading the
Bible from the Gospel of Matthew.

00:14:22.496 --> 00:14:26.332
Someone should have taught you
this at some point in your life,

00:14:26.332 --> 00:14:29.530
and if they didn't, I'm sorry,
that's a significant oversight.

00:14:30.190 --> 00:14:32.087
Why not from the beginning?

00:14:32.087 --> 00:14:37.399
Well, by the time you get to Leviticus
with all the animal sacrifices and

00:14:37.399 --> 00:14:41.573
those octopuses and tadpoles, I
just close the Bible, don't you?

00:14:41.573 --> 00:14:46.127
I can't, it makes me sick,
I don't like the drawings, I

00:14:46.127 --> 00:14:50.680
can't see those sea creatures,
I don't have to enjoy the Bible.

00:14:50.680 --> 00:14:54.475
And a lot of vocabulary, aorists,
imperfects, all those things

00:14:54.475 --> 00:14:58.270
we don't regularly use in our
everyday speech, discourage us.

00:14:58.530 --> 00:15:04.270
And I don't want to go through with
you now how you should read the

00:15:04.270 --> 00:15:09.246
Bible, there are hundreds of places
where you can learn that, but I

00:15:09.246 --> 00:15:14.221
actually just want to finish with one
thing: that we be those evangelical

00:15:14.221 --> 00:15:16.135
teachers, like Saint Anthony was.

00:15:16.135 --> 00:15:20.345
We constantly call each other
to be holy, and that's great.

00:15:20.345 --> 00:15:24.555
And I think somehow that from
the Second Vatican Council to

00:15:24.555 --> 00:15:28.765
today, in the past 50-60 years,
at least we've understood that.

00:15:28.765 --> 00:15:32.179
It took us 60 years, people of God.

00:15:32.179 --> 00:15:36.874
For us to understand that we
are all called to holiness.

00:15:36.874 --> 00:15:39.861
Just that one sentence to sink in.

00:15:39.861 --> 00:15:44.983
Maybe in the next 50 years,
we'll realize that we are all

00:15:44.983 --> 00:15:47.544
called to be witnesses of faith.

00:15:47.544 --> 00:15:50.531
We might not be martyrs, probably not.

00:15:50.531 --> 00:15:54.800
But tell me you've never been
persecuted for your faith.

00:15:54.900 --> 00:16:00.633
Tell me you've never felt that look
when someone glares at you for making

00:16:00.633 --> 00:16:03.909
the sign of the cross in a restaurant.

00:16:03.909 --> 00:16:07.186
That you've never felt
judged for dressing modestly.

00:16:07.186 --> 00:16:11.691
Today, people aren't judged for dressing
immodestly, but for dressing modestly,

00:16:11.691 --> 00:16:17.015
and then they say, "Look, a nun." It's
a completely distorted value system.

00:16:17.115 --> 00:16:22.941
Tell me you've never felt people
giving you strange looks if they hear

00:16:22.941 --> 00:16:29.216
Božja pobjeda or Amoroze or whoever is
playing in your headphones on the tram.

00:16:29.216 --> 00:16:36.387
We feel it, and we feel it very strongly,
how many relationships have broken up when

00:16:36.387 --> 00:16:39.525
the question of premarital purity came up.

00:16:39.525 --> 00:16:46.248
It's better to break up early, as someone
who deals with a dreadful matter here,

00:16:46.248 --> 00:16:51.626
which is the annulment of Christian
marriages, that's one of my jobs.

00:16:51.626 --> 00:16:58.349
Believe me, it's better to break up in
time if the differences are too great.

00:16:58.349 --> 00:17:01.885
Nothing significant will change
when you receive the sacrament

00:17:01.885 --> 00:17:03.456
of marriage, believe me.

00:17:03.456 --> 00:17:06.992
Did I change a lot when I was ordained?

00:17:06.992 --> 00:17:13.277
Not really, I'd say, maybe I just became
more aware of how I was all along?

00:17:13.277 --> 00:17:14.063
That's debatable.

00:17:14.063 --> 00:17:18.777
And that's why today I invite us
to be those evangelical teachers.

00:17:18.777 --> 00:17:19.169
Fr.

00:17:19.169 --> 00:17:23.275
Today, Stjepan touched on a very
important matter in his sermon, and

00:17:23.275 --> 00:17:27.724
that important matter is to stop
being afraid to talk about our faith.

00:17:27.724 --> 00:17:30.461
Let's stop being afraid
to witness our faith.

00:17:30.461 --> 00:17:32.172
Who are we afraid of?

00:17:32.172 --> 00:17:34.567
Who is afraid in front of us?

00:17:34.567 --> 00:17:38.331
Who is afraid to wave their
ideology in front of us?

00:17:38.331 --> 00:17:38.673
Who?

00:17:38.673 --> 00:17:42.094
But Christianity is not an
ideology; Christianity is a person.

00:17:42.534 --> 00:17:46.541
Not one person but three
persons in one God: the Father,

00:17:46.541 --> 00:17:48.726
the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

00:17:48.726 --> 00:17:53.825
And that is why it is very, very
important, more important today than ever,

00:17:53.825 --> 00:17:56.374
to seriously embrace the word of God.

00:17:56.374 --> 00:17:58.923
To seriously accept the word of God.

00:17:58.923 --> 00:18:04.022
There is no question you can ask God
that isn't answered in the Bible.

00:18:04.022 --> 00:18:07.664
Your day cannot start without
at least going online and

00:18:07.664 --> 00:18:12.035
listening to the reflection of
the day, the gospel of the day.

00:18:13.035 --> 00:18:19.195
Your grandparents and mine might have
had an excuse back then, maybe even my

00:18:19.195 --> 00:18:24.915
parents, maybe not yours, but my parents,
because, well, there wasn't a way.

00:18:24.915 --> 00:18:29.755
There was no religious education
in schools, no internet, no books,

00:18:29.755 --> 00:18:35.035
no literature from which they could
learn... Today, don't make me laugh.

00:18:35.764 --> 00:18:38.959
That we today cannot
seriously study our faith.

00:18:38.959 --> 00:18:45.748
And as Fr. Stjepan often says, you
come to me and say, so I will say it

00:18:45.748 --> 00:18:52.137
now, you come to me and say, in the
family, when we discuss or in society

00:18:52.137 --> 00:18:56.929
about faith, they all present some
arguments and I stay silent, like

00:18:56.929 --> 00:18:59.725
a fish out of water, just gaping.

00:19:00.439 --> 00:19:00.894
Mava.

00:19:00.894 --> 00:19:05.888
Because what will you speak
from when your head is empty?

00:19:05.888 --> 00:19:08.612
When you don't know about faith.

00:19:08.612 --> 00:19:14.060
When we have read the Catechism of
the Catholic Church from beginning

00:19:14.060 --> 00:19:16.784
to end, and then what happens?

00:19:16.784 --> 00:19:21.325
You go to dnevno.hr, one of
the most desperate criminal

00:19:21.325 --> 00:19:24.049
portals that exist in the world.

00:19:24.049 --> 00:19:25.411
Remember that well.

00:19:25.411 --> 00:19:28.589
Sensationalist click-baiters,
plain and simple, nothing else.

00:19:28.589 --> 00:19:33.129
And there it says, the
church banned blah blah blah.

00:19:33.129 --> 00:19:35.898
And we, oh look, the church forbade it.

00:19:35.898 --> 00:19:40.052
Or, the church allowed it, oh look,
the naughty church allowed it.

00:19:40.052 --> 00:19:41.782
And what do you do?

00:19:41.782 --> 00:19:43.513
Share, share, share, share, share.

00:19:43.513 --> 00:19:47.666
You know when you get those annoying
messages forwarded many times, I

00:19:47.666 --> 00:19:52.512
break out in hives when I see that,
I know immediately what it is.

00:19:52.512 --> 00:19:57.703
As soon as I see it’s been forwarded many
times, without any thought, without any

00:19:57.703 --> 00:20:01.857
responsibility, without any sense that
what you, as a Catholic, forwarded to

00:20:01.857 --> 00:20:07.395
someone who isn’t, how much your word is
worth in their eyes and in their ears.

00:20:08.215 --> 00:20:13.970
It is not insignificant what I, as
a friar, say because of what I wear.

00:20:13.970 --> 00:20:18.574
I realized this 17 years ago
when I came to this monastery.

00:20:18.574 --> 00:20:22.795
Similarly, it is not insignificant
what you say to each other

00:20:22.795 --> 00:20:25.097
because they know you come here.

00:20:25.097 --> 00:20:29.318
The standards are higher and the
responsibility before God is greater.

00:20:29.318 --> 00:20:35.074
This is what I would like us to take
from the Holy Scriptures about the

00:20:35.074 --> 00:20:37.760
theology of Saint Anthony and his wisdom.

00:20:38.520 --> 00:20:43.241
Do not be afraid to open
your ears to the Holy Spirit.

00:20:43.241 --> 00:20:44.028
Jesus promised.

00:20:44.028 --> 00:20:49.537
When you don't know what to say, when
they bring you before kings—though we

00:20:49.537 --> 00:20:55.046
probably won't be brought before kings,
as that's a thing of the past—but when

00:20:55.046 --> 00:21:00.554
they crucify you here, crucify you here,
say this about you, say that, publicly

00:21:00.554 --> 00:21:03.702
call you out, don't be afraid, He says.

00:21:03.702 --> 00:21:05.670
It's expected, it will happen.

00:21:06.130 --> 00:21:07.035
Jesus said it.

00:21:07.035 --> 00:21:09.148
Do not plan your defense in advance.

00:21:09.148 --> 00:21:13.375
Even you, when you are with your families,
don't You know when someone... Attacks

00:21:13.375 --> 00:21:18.205
you and then you don't know what to
say at that moment, and then you go,

00:21:18.205 --> 00:21:23.639
I don't know, take a shower or go to
training or go for a walk and then it

00:21:23.639 --> 00:21:28.469
comes to your mind, oh, I could have
said this, oh, I should have said that,

00:21:28.469 --> 00:21:30.885
oh, and this, oh how I could have...

00:21:31.525 --> 00:21:37.981
No, if you were supposed to
say it, you would have said it.

00:21:37.981 --> 00:21:39.967
No, let God lead.

00:21:39.967 --> 00:21:44.934
At that moment, maybe that
person didn't need a dragon.

00:21:44.934 --> 00:21:50.893
They needed a lamb, and you'll
evangelize more when you're a lamb.

00:21:50.893 --> 00:21:57.350
But sometimes you do need to be
a dragon, not the dragon from

00:21:57.350 --> 00:22:03.310
Revelation, but a force in words,
to be resolute, to be clear.

00:22:03.669 --> 00:22:07.056
And you serve it and then you eat it.

00:22:07.056 --> 00:22:11.196
It's like when you eat beef
that hasn't been cooked well,

00:22:11.196 --> 00:22:13.454
it's like chewing on a shoe.

00:22:13.454 --> 00:22:15.336
That rubber, chew, chew, chew.

00:22:15.336 --> 00:22:17.594
Sometimes that's the Word of God.

00:22:17.594 --> 00:22:22.486
No one ever promised that the Word
of God would be easily digestible,

00:22:22.486 --> 00:22:24.744
like millet or some light proteins.

00:22:24.744 --> 00:22:30.389
Sometimes the Word of God is really hard
on the stomach, and you shouldn't think

00:22:30.389 --> 00:22:33.399
you're on the wrong path because of that.

00:22:33.800 --> 00:22:38.324
You don't fully understand why the
church teaches this or that way, kneel.

00:22:38.324 --> 00:22:42.152
I studied my theology on my knees,
before the Blessed Sacrament.

00:22:42.152 --> 00:22:46.676
And I held a few of my books
like this before the sacrament

00:22:46.676 --> 00:22:48.416
and asked, what is this?

00:22:48.416 --> 00:22:50.504
Not, what is this, I said.

00:22:53.175 --> 00:22:54.172
What is this?

00:22:54.172 --> 00:22:56.166
I don't understand any of it.

00:22:56.166 --> 00:23:01.152
And he is silent, and the book is
silent, and I am silent, and nothing.

00:23:01.152 --> 00:23:02.814
I continue on, still kneeling.

00:23:03.034 --> 00:23:07.033
I can't be stubborn, and
neither can I. I will kneel

00:23:07.033 --> 00:23:09.578
here until it makes sense to me.

00:23:09.578 --> 00:23:14.303
That's what's important to us,
and I want you to take that with

00:23:14.303 --> 00:23:18.302
you as we prepare for our beloved
seventh St. Anthony's walk.

00:23:18.302 --> 00:23:20.119
Now, I will stop here.

00:23:20.119 --> 00:23:25.572
I will finish with the words of St.
Anthony who says this: If you preach

00:23:25.572 --> 00:23:27.389
Jesus, he softens hardened hearts.

00:23:27.389 --> 00:23:31.817
If you call upon Him, your
bitter temptations become sweet.

00:23:31.817 --> 00:23:35.801
If you think about Him,
He enlightens your heart.

00:23:35.801 --> 00:23:39.785
If you read about Jesus,
He nourishes your mind.

00:23:39.785 --> 00:23:43.770
Thank you very much and
have a pleasant evening.

